<DOC><DOCNO>WSJ920203-0138</DOCNO><DOCID>920203-0138.</DOCID><HL>   International:   Finnish Firm to Replace Plant</HL><DATE>02/03/92</DATE><SO>WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), NO PAGE CITATION</SO><CO>   C.NES</CO><MS>ENERGY (ENE)</MS><IN>OIL-INTEGRATED MAJORS (OIL)PETROLEUM (PET)</IN><NS>PETROLEUM MARKET (PET)</NS><RE>EUROPE (EU)FINLAND (FI)SCANDINAVIA (SCA)</RE><LP>   STOCKHOLM -- Neste Oy, a Finnish state-controlled oil andchemicals group, said it will replace the existing powerplant at its main refinery in Porvoo, Finland, with a newgas-based unit at a projected cost of about $670 million.   The plans to upgrade power generation capacity areintended to meet growing energy needs at the Porvoo complexstemming from increased production of low-pollution vehiclefuels, Neste said.</LP><TEXT>   &quot;The new technology proposed for the plant will alsoreduce power generation-related emissions at the site,&quot; thegroup said. Design and construction work is estimated to takeabout four years and provide a total of about 3,000 man-yearsof employment, the group said.</TEXT></DOC>